            <div class="mb-2">
                <span class="fw-bold">üéØ Interview Question:</span>
                <span class="fst-italic">"What is the difference between Scoped and Transient services?"</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ms-4">
                <strong>Answer:</strong>
                <ul class="mb-0 mt-2">
                    <li><strong>Transient:</strong> A new instance is created every time it's requested. Use for lightweight, stateless services.</li>
                    <li><strong>Scoped:</strong> One instance per HTTP request/scope. All requests within the same scope get the same instance. Use for services that maintain state during a request.</li>
                    <li><strong>Singleton:</strong> One instance for the entire application lifetime. Shared across all requests. Use for stateless services or shared caches.</li>
                    <li><strong>Key Difference:</strong> Transient = always new, Scoped = new per request, Singleton = one forever.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

